# META-TEMPLATE: Base Template Structure
# This is a template FOR creating templates
#
# Purpose: Defines the standard structure all MGFTS templates should follow
# Layer: 3 (Meta-Governance)
# Version: 1.0.0
#
# Usage: When creating a new template, use this meta-template to ensure
#        consistency with MGFTS template standards.
#
# Variables in this meta-template:
#   {{TEMPLATE_TYPE}}: Type of template (e.g., "python_module", "documentation")
#   {{TEMPLATE_DESCRIPTION}}: What this template generates
#   {{FILE_EXTENSION}}: Extension for generated files (e.g., ".py", ".md")
#   {{TEMPLATE_CATEGORY}}: Category (code|config|docs|test)

# =============================================================================
# TEMPLATE HEADER SECTION
# All templates MUST include a header explaining what they generate
# =============================================================================

{{HEADER_COMMENT_START}}{{TEMPLATE_DESCRIPTION}}

{{PURPOSE_SECTION}}

Author: {{AUTHOR}}
Created: {{CREATED_DATE}}
Version: {{VERSION}}
Layer: {{MGFTS_LAYER}}
{{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED VARIABLES SECTION
# All templates MUST document their required variables
# =============================================================================

{{COMMENT_START}}
Required Template Variables:
  {{VARIABLE_LIST}}

Optional Template Variables:
  {{OPTIONAL_VARIABLE_LIST}}

Example Usage:
  {{USAGE_EXAMPLE}}
{{COMMENT_END}}

# =============================================================================
# TEMPLATE BODY SECTION
# The actual content that will be generated
# =============================================================================

{{TEMPLATE_SPECIFIC_CONTENT}}

# =============================================================================
# TEMPLATE FOOTER SECTION (optional)
# =============================================================================

{{FOOTER_CONTENT}}

# =============================================================================
# META-TEMPLATE VALIDATION RULES
# =============================================================================
#
# When creating a template from this meta-template, ensure:
#
# 1. HEADER COMPLETENESS
#    - Template description is clear and concise
#    - Purpose explains what gets generated
#    - Author and version are specified
#
# 2. VARIABLE DOCUMENTATION
#    - All variables are listed
#    - Variable purposes are explained
#    - Example values are provided
#
# 3. TEMPLATE BODY
#    - Uses consistent variable naming (UPPER_SNAKE_CASE)
#    - Variables are enclosed in {{double braces}}
#    - No hard-coded values that should be variables
#
# 4. SYNTACTIC CORRECTNESS
#    - Generated files will be syntactically valid
#    - Comment syntax matches target language
#    - Indentation is consistent
#
# 5. COMPLETENESS
#    - Template generates a fully functional file
#    - Includes error handling (if applicable)
#    - Includes documentation (if applicable)
#    - Includes examples (if applicable)
#
# 6. MGFTS COMPLIANCE
#    - Template output complies with Layer 1 structural requirements
#    - Template output complies with Layer 2 governance requirements
#    - Template itself is documented in template manifest
#
# =============================================================================

# Meta-Template Substitution Markers:
#
# {{HEADER_COMMENT_START}} → Language-specific comment start
# {{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}   → Language-specific comment end (if needed)
# {{COMMENT_START}}        → Multi-line comment start
# {{COMMENT_END}}          → Multi-line comment end
# {{PURPOSE_SECTION}}      → Detailed purpose text
# {{VARIABLE_LIST}}        → Comma-separated required variables
# {{OPTIONAL_VARIABLE_LIST}} → Comma-separated optional variables
# {{USAGE_EXAMPLE}}        → Example of how to use the template
# {{TEMPLATE_SPECIFIC_CONTENT}} → The core template body
# {{FOOTER_CONTENT}}       → Optional footer (license, attribution, etc.)

# =============================================================================
# EXAMPLES OF LANGUAGE-SPECIFIC SUBSTITUTIONS
# =============================================================================

# For Python templates:
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_START}} = '"""'
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}   = '"""'
#   {{COMMENT_START}}        = '"""'
#   {{COMMENT_END}}          = '"""'

# For JavaScript templates:
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_START}} = '/**\n * '
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}   = '\n */'
#   {{COMMENT_START}}        = '/*'
#   {{COMMENT_END}}          = '*/'

# For Configuration templates (JSON5, YAML):
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_START}} = '// '
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}   = ''
#   {{COMMENT_START}}        = '// '
#   {{COMMENT_END}}          = ''

# For Markdown templates:
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_START}} = '<!--\n'
#   {{HEADER_COMMENT_END}}   = '\n-->'
#   {{COMMENT_START}}        = '<!--'
#   {{COMMENT_END}}          = '-->'
